LAFIA â€“ The North Central Zonal office of the Federal Radio Cooperation of Nigeria (FRCN) on Thursday threatened legal action against Nasarawa State Board of Internal Revenue Service and Nasarawa Broadcasting Service (NBS) for peddling fake news in the country. The letter demand retraction of the said report within 48 hours and tender an apology through their medium and other platform. The FRCN in a letter by North Central Zonal Office addressed to Nasarawa State Internal Revenue Service and Nasarawa Broadcasting Service NBS said that the said story was done by Mr. Godspower Eded, an employee of the organisation who in his report on the 7th-8th referred to FRCN as peddlers of fake news.